		<!-- message -->
		<div>Adds happen.  Maybe not always suppose to but they do.<br />
<br />
I am a shadowknight who doensn't have dreaded gaze yet.  <br />
<br />
It is necessary for me sometimes to aggro several mobs on incoming during raids to save healer and chanters from getting smacked.  Normally I just aggro what I can, but single mobs at time.  I use the new terror, have used fear in the past.  I keep my eyes out for mouse targetting (but I am always lagging! this doesn't work well) , have some assist keys made for monks, have F8 to target closest mob ready to go.  I always get a spell haste to help cast faster.  I try to be in close proximity to mobs when possible.  If all that fails I seek out mobs that may have run over to healers, chanters, shammies etc and get aggro from them (not damage aggro).<br />
<br />
I can't seem though in some situations to prevent some serious deaths.  I have tried our other area of effect spells, but they don't seem to work for me.<br />
<br />
I am wondering if scrolling through the NPCS (I confess I am not sure how to set this up, what is the name of that function) would help.<br />
<br />
What else can help me do this?  Once I get aggro, I keep it, and my healers keep me up 99.9% of the time when I do without dying themselves.  <br />
<br />
Any suggestions on how to improve this?  I know it can be done.  I see other SK's do it all of the time!</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
