		<!-- message -->
		<div>Not sure if this will help you, but has come in handy for me in some tight battles.<br />
<br />
Usually when I Tank, as we all SK's know, our Snare/DoT is one of our fastest ways of getting agro and keeping it, with the help of our Terror, and Voice line of spells.<br />
<br />
I have always noticed that even when 2 or more mobs are incoming, and I tag the mob(one that the Puller pulls) with a Snare/DoT all of his other friends, don't seem to like it and tends to head straight for you.  Yes, Yes I know, once the Ench or someone else throws a slow or some other form of Debuff, the other mobs will now put them higher on the hate lists and head for that person, where as the first mob I taged is still comming to me.  Now where does this all boil down too?  I have been able to get agro on atleast 3 mobs for sure by using this.  Puller pulls, I snare mob, and Wham here comes his two buddies who are really pissed off at me.  The first mob is snared and will take some time to get there:-  the other two one I hit with Terror spell, and the other I try my best to tag it, and hit Taunt.  Usually works for me, but it does fail sometimes, I know a pure caster might be really happy for that extra second he has to get mob tied down.  The only places of late where I see I am having trouble doing this is in the OoW, and GoD zones, where the mobs run Like Grease Lightning, so you really don't have time to tag em all.  In all it's a nice little way to grab agro off of a couple mobs when they are incoming.<br />
<br />
I would like to know though if anyone has been able to come up with a really good way of doing it in OoW, and GoD zones,,, Dam mobs are just too fast.<br />
<br />
Nice post, will keep reading.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
